1. Data Preperation

1.1 Read the Data

InfoSeek <- as.data.frame(read_excel("InfoSeek.xlsx"))
Collab <- as.data.frame(read_excel("Collab.xlsx"))
## New names:
## * `` -> `..1`
Attributes <- as.data.frame(read_excel("Attributes.xlsx"))

1.2 Create the Network Objects

1.2.1 Create the adjancy matrices

IS.m <- data.matrix(InfoSeek[,-1])
rownames(IS.m) <- colnames(InfoSeek)[-1]
IS.m <- ifelse(IS.m > 3, 1, 0)
diag(IS.m) <- 0

CO.m <- data.matrix(Collab[,-1])
rownames(CO.m) <- colnames(Collab)[-1]
CO.m <- (CO.m + t(CO.m)) / 2
CO.m <- ifelse(CO.m > 3, 1, 0)
diag(CO.m) <- 0

1.2.2 Create the Network objects

IS <- graph.adjacency(IS.m)
CO <- graph.adjacency(CO.m, mode = "undirected")

1.2.3 Add attributes

for(cn in colnames(Attributes)[-1]) {
     IS <- set_vertex_attr(IS, cn, 1:nrow(Attributes), value = Attributes[,cn])
     CO <- set_vertex_attr(CO, cn, 1:nrow(Attributes), value = Attributes[,cn])
}

1.2.4 Check the networks

summary(IS)

2.1.1.3 Degree, Average Degree and Degree Distribution

For in-degree

# in-degree
indegree_IS <- igraph::degree(IS, mode = "in")
# average in-degree
mean(indegree_IS)
## [1] 18.73394
# in-degree distribution
indegree_dist_IS <- igraph::degree.distribution(IS, mode = "in", cumulative = FALSE)
# cumulative in-degree distribution
indegree_cdist_IS <- igraph::degree.distribution(IS, mode = "in", cumulative = TRUE)
# plot the cumulative in-degree distribution
plot(indegree_cdist_IS, log = "xy", ylim = c(.01, 5), bg = "black", pch = 21,
     xlab = "In-Degree", ylab = "Cumulative Frequency")

For out-degree

# out-degree
outdegree_IS <- igraph::degree(IS, mode = "out")
# average out-degree

Density are Reduced to Zero or Increase to One

bimage[bimage < den] <- 0
bimage[is.nan(bimage)] <- 1

View the Plot

set.seed(1234)
gplot(bimage, diag = TRUE, 
      edge.lwd = bimage*10, 
      label = colnames(bimage),
      vertex.cex = sqrt(table(b$block.membership)),
      gmode = "digraph", vertex.sides = 50, 
      vertex.col = gray(1 - diag(bimage)/2))
